sublime-jekyll changelog
========================

## v2.2.2 (2015-03-03)

- Fix #30
- Add support for opening posts/drafts in subdirectories
- Add support for promoting drafts to posts while maintaining directory tree

## v2.2.1 (2015-02-08)

- Closes PR #27
- Added support for finding Jekyll folders in active view
    - Enable in user or project settings
    - Will attempt to recursively find the `_posts` and `_drafts` directories
    - Falls back to project settings if none are found

## v2.1.3 (2015-01-28)

- Closes #25
- Fix ST2 bug with format strings (related to Python 2.6)

## v2.1.2 (2015-01-18)

- Closes #24
- Remove date/datetime keybindings that clash with ST defaults

## v2.1.2 (2014-12-17)

- Closes #23
- Add support for multi-level dictionary in front-matter defaults
- Update JekyllPostFrontmatterCommand to use insert_snippet

## v2.1.0 (2014-12-07)

- Implement new post front-matter extras (closes #22)
- Allow for default post keys to be hidden using `null`
- Update default Jekyll settings file to include instructions
- Small changes to README

## v2.0.8 (2014-11-30)

- Fixes #14 with messages directory naming convention (only affects Linux systems)

## v2.0.7

- Merge pull request #18 from calledT/master

## v2.0.6 (2014-11-01)

- Merge pull request #17 from @fk128
- Fixed duplicates from showing in Quick Panel
- Added directory check (in cases where drafts/posts paths do not exist)
- Added sorting of posts by last modified date

## v2.0.5 (2014-10-16)

- Fixed ST2 specific bug in run_commands and set_timeout

## v2.0.4 (2014-09-04)

- Fixed issue with trailing commas in commands

## v2.0.3 (2014-07-31)

- Small changes to default settings and front-matter snippet
- Added screenshot for new github.io project site page
- Added support for install and update messages
- Small updates to README.md

## v2.0.2 (2014-07-04)

- Added support for converting drafts to posts (closes #11)
- Small updates to README.md
- Small bug fixes to "open" commands

## v2.0.1 (2014-06-18)

- Fixed #7
- Fixed #9
- Added support for ST2 (closes #8)
- Added default keymaps back

## v2.0.0 (2014-06-16)

- Added Jekyll 2.0 snippets and completions
- Added brand new commands for post interaction
- Clean up code in most files for easier reading
- Remove default keybindings

## v1.0.1 (2014-01-17)

- Added documentation for configuring a Jekyll build system
- Small updates to `README.md` and `Main.sublime-menu`

## v1.0.0 (2014-01-12)

- Added platform specific key bindings to menu (previously missing)
- Added Textile (Jekyll) syntax file, and updated snippets/completions scope
- Added Textile comments and syntax specific preferences
- Added text.textile file to Tests directory
- Bumping version officially to v1.0.0

## v0.1.2 (2014-01-05)

- Fixed #2 (updates to snippets)

## v0.1.1 (2014-01-04)

- Updated `insert_date` command to support multiple formats
- Updated syntax settings in all snippet files
- Updated snippets
- Updated `README.md` documentation
- Added keymap files

## v0.1.0 (2014-01-04)

- Initial commit
